(25, 2500, 2001, 'chevrolet', 'silverado 1500', 'fair', '8 cylinders', 'gas', '220000', 'clean', 'automatic', 'rwd', 5, 'full-size', 'pickup', 'silver', 'https://images.craigslist.org/00L0L_6yyVIT0W9nz_600x450.jpg', '2001 SILVERADO 1500 Ext Cab Shortbed. $2500 cash, 5.3V8/Auto. 220K miles, PS, PB, PW, PL, AC, Cruise. Headache rack and toolbox included. Clean title.\n\nThe Good: Everything works. Clean interior, no rips (yet). It\'s been a super-reliable work truck for me - Starts every time, Runs great, Drives and Stops straight, Good tires. Aftermarket radio w/ cd and bluetooth (I have the original radio/cd player if you want it). Since I\'ve owned it (the last 10 years and 110K miles), it\'s been well-maintained - regular oil changes, at 200K miles all fluids were changed, trans was serviced, and the serp. belt, spark plugs, and 2 coils were replaced. It averages 16-17 mpg as long as I\'ve owned it. It doesn\'t burn oil, but it will consume about a quart every 5K mile change.\n\nThe Bad: The previous owners were not kind to it - it got hit on the right front side, got the fender replaced but never painted, the bed and rear bumper have their share of dings/dents/scratches. It was repossessed and I bought it from the bank. Then, 6 years ago a deer committed suicide by running into the drivers fender and door, but that was properly repaired. Currently, the front wheel hubs, the knock sensors, and the water pump need replacing - I already have the parts on hand. The ABS and Brake system lights come on about half the time, I\'ve been told the problem is in the ABS motor relays under the cab, which is a common issue with these trucks - I\'ve never had any problems with the brakes functioning.  I have an OBD2 scanner and am happy to scan and show any codes in the truck.\n\nThe Ugly: See the photos of the right front corner and bed sides / rear.\n\nSummary: That\'s all I can think of to write down about it. It\'s been a solid reliable work truck for me, and I figure it\'s got probably another 75-100K miles in it - but I inherited a newer pickup with less miles, so it\'s time for this one to find work elsewhere. I think it\'d make a great work, farm, or first vehicle (scratch it and not worry!)\n\nCall or text me at 325-201 Twenty Thirteen. I\'m asking $2500, and I\'m happy to meet you just about anywhere in the Abilene / Buffalo Gap area and show you the truck, so please don\'t call and ask me \"what my bottom dollar is.\" Trying to deal over the phone without even seeing what you\'re dealing with - that\'s just silly.\n\nAnd No, I don\'t need any help selling it.'),
